  where `D(ρ_n || σ''_ε_n)` is the Kullback-Leibler divergence between `ρ_n` and a specific sequence of "pinched" states `σ''_ε_n`.
  This is a key result in the theory of hypothesis testing and information theory, establishing bounds on the rate of convergence of the relative entropy.
